Package: intersectr
Type: Package
Title: Spatiotemporal Intersections
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: person("David", "Blodgett", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "dblodgett@usgs.gov")
Depends:
    R (>= 3.0)
Description: Package for intersecting spatiotemporal attribute data. The primary 
    emphasis is on gridded time-series data such as meteorological forcings that 
    need to be intersected with a spatial modeling mesh or set of spatial modeling units.
URL: https://github.com/USGS-R/intersectr
BugReports: https://github.com/USGS-R/intersectr/issues
Imports: sf, stars, dplyr, RNetCDF, ncmeta, areal, data.table, ncdfgeom, rgdal
Remotes: hypertidy/ncmeta, USGS-R/ncdfgeom, cran/rgdal@1.3-9, slu-openGIS/areal@v0.1.3
Suggests: testthat, tibble, knitr, rmarkdown
License: CC0
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
